#, no-c-format
msgid "Show help about options."
msgstr "Mostra la guida sulle opzioni."

#. Tag: term
#: man-meinproc6.1.docbook:101
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-v</option><option>--version</option>"
msgstr "<option>-v</option><option>--version</option>"

#. Tag: para
#: man-meinproc6.1.docbook:103
#, no-c-format
msgid "Show version information."
msgstr "Mostra le informazioni sulla versione."

#. Tag: title
#: man-meinproc6.1.docbook:114
#, no-c-format
msgid "Application Options"
msgstr "Opzioni dell'applicazione"

#. Tag: term
#: man-meinproc6.1.docbook:118
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>--cache</option> <parameter>file</parameter>"
msgstr "<option>--cache</option> <parameter>file</parameter>"

#. Tag: para
#: man-meinproc6.1.docbook:120
#, no-c-format
msgid "Create a cache file for the document."
msgstr "Crea un file di cache per il documento."

#. Tag: option
#: man-meinproc6.1.docbook:127
#, no-c-format
msgid "--check"
msgstr "--check"

#. Tag: para
#: man-meinproc6.1.docbook:129
#, no-c-format
msgid "Check the document for validity."
msgstr "Controlla la validità del documento."

#. Tag: screen
#: man-meinproc6.1.docbook:130
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The output can be a bit daunting, since one small mistake can cause a "
"cascade of errors. \n"
"The trick is to look at the first error, fix that error, save the file, and "
"run <command>meinproc6</command> again."
msgstr ""
"L'output può essere un po' confuso, perché un errorino può causare una "
"cascata di errori.\n"
"Il trucco è cercare il primo errore, correggerlo, salvare il file, e far "
"ripartire <command>meinproc6</command>."

#. Tag: term
#: man-meinproc6.1.docbook:135
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<option>-o</option>, <option>--output</option><parameter> file</parameter>"
msgstr ""
"<option>-o</option>, <option>--output</option> <parameter>file</parameter>"

#. Tag: para
#: man-meinproc6.1.docbook:137
#, no-c-format
msgid "Output whole document to <parameter>file</parameter>."
msgstr "Metti l'intero documento su <parameter>file</parameter>."

#. Tag: option
#: man-meinproc6.1.docbook:144
#, no-c-format
msgid "--stdout"
msgstr "--stdout"

#. Tag: para
#: man-meinproc6.1.docbook:146
#, no-c-format
msgid "Output whole document to stdout."
msgstr "Metti l'intero documento sul flusso stdout."

#. Tag: term
#: man-meinproc6.1.docbook:153
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>--stylesheet</option> <parameter>xsl</parameter>"
msgstr "<option>--stylesheet</option> <parameter>xsl</parameter>"

#. Tag: para
#: man-meinproc6.1.docbook:155
#, no-c-format
msgid "Stylesheet to use."
msgstr "Foglio di stile da usare."

#. Tag: term
#: man-meinproc6.1.docbook:162
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>--srcdir</option> <parameter>dir</parameter>"
msgstr "<option>--srcdir</option> <parameter>cartella</parameter>"

#. Tag: para
#: man-meinproc6.1.docbook:164
#, no-c-format
msgid "Set the root directory to look for kdoctools."
msgstr "Imposta la cartella radice in cui cercare kdoctools."

#. Tag: term
#: man-meinproc6.1.docbook:171
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>--param</option> key=value"
msgstr "<option>--param</option> chiave=valore"

#. Tag: para
#: man-meinproc6.1.docbook:173
#, no-c-format
msgid "Set parameters to pass to the stylesheet."
msgstr "Imposta i parametri da passare al foglio di stile."

#. Tag: title
#: man-meinproc6.1.docbook:184
#, no-c-format
msgid "Usage"
msgstr "Uso"

#. Tag: para
#: man-meinproc6.1.docbook:185
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The most common way to run <command>meinproc6</command> is simply as "
"<literallayout>\n"
"<userinput><command>meinproc6</command> <replaceable>docbook-file</"
"replaceable>\n"
"</userinput>\n"
"</literallayout> where <replaceable>docbook-file</replaceable> is usually "
"index.docbook. This command creates &HTML; pages from the DocBook file. Note "
"that these pages are only viewable in &kde;-based browsers (like "
"&konqueror;)."
msgstr ""
"Il modo più comune di eseguire <command>meinproc6</command> è semplicemente "
"come <literallayout>\n"
"<userinput><command>meinproc6</command> <replaceable>file_docbook</"
"replaceable>\n"
"</userinput>\n"
"</literallayout> dove <replaceable>file_docbook</replaceable> è di solito "
"<filename>index.docbook</filename>. Questo comando crea pagine &HTML; dal "
"file DocBook. Nota che queste pagine sono visibili solo in browser basati su "
"&kde; (come &konqueror;)."

#. Tag: para
#: man-meinproc6.1.docbook:192
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you need to view the &HTML; output in another browser (for example, if "
"you're placing it on line), use <literallayout>\n"
"<userinput><command>meinproc6</command> --stylesheet <replaceable>stylesheet-"
"name</replaceable> <replaceable>docbook-file</replaceable>\n"
"</userinput>\n"
"</literallayout> where <replaceable>stylesheet-name</replaceable> is the "
"full path to one of the &XSL; stylesheets in &lt;"
"kdoctools_installation_prefix&gt;/share/kf5/kdoctools/customization/. To "
"produce output suitable for the web, you can use <command>kde-web.xsl</"
"command> or <command>kde-chunk-online.xsl</command>. See the "
"<filename>README</filename> file in that directory for more details."
msgstr ""
"Se devi vedere il risultato &HTML; in un altro browser (per esempio, se lo "
"metti in rete), usa <literallayout>\n"
"<userinput><command>meinproc6</command> --stylesheet "
"<replaceable>nome_foglio_di_stile</replaceable> <replaceable>file_docbook</"
"replaceable>\n"
"</userinput>\n"
"</literallayout> where <replaceable>nome_foglio_di_stile</replaceable> è il "
"percorso completo a uno dei fogli di stile &XSL; in <filename class="
"\"directory\">&lt;kdoctools_installation_prefix&gt;/share/kf5/kdoctools/"
"customization</filename>. Per produrre documenti adatti al Web, puoi usare "
"<filename>kde-web.xsl</filename> o <filename>kde-chunk-online.xsl</"
"filename>. Vedi il file <filename>README</filename> in quella cartella per "
"maggiori dettagli."

